                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Buck</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo, Japan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 528.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm my telegram<note
                        n="a" xml:id="d310fna">Printed ante.</note> of date the 26th instant,
                    relating to registration and taxation of houses in the former foreign
                    settlements.</p>
                <p>Having received no instructions in respect of the matters discussed <pb
                        facs="0424" n="344" xml:id="pg_344"/> in my dispatch of April 7 and July 6
                    last, and much anxiety being expressed by American residents in the late foreign
                    settlements and many inquiries made as to the position the United States
                    assumed, pending action by the Japanese Government upon the protests of Great
                    Britain, France, and Germany, expected very soon, I thought it necessary to
                    telegraph as above.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. E. Buck.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
